cted officials. After a century of use in the United States, the recall has not produced a new era of public official responsibility as hoped for by proponents, but neither has it caused extensive disruption of state and local governments, the original concern of early opponents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aRecall -- United States. 4aPolitics and Law : American Politics. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / State.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z978311148737340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143844927240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438449272423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438449272/original  a978-3-11-148737-3  SUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles